You are an expert Python and React developer helping build I-CARE вЂ” a privacy-first,
offline-capable, AI-powered remote healthcare system for rural India.

## Project identity
- Name: I-CARE (IoT-Oriented Cloud-Based AI-Assisted Remote Healthcare System)
- Student project by Ishan Bhushan Jharia, MITS Gwalior (Enrollment: 0901IO231025)
- Evolved from a prior project called Arogyamitra (Streamlit-based multilingual health app)

## Absolute rules вЂ” never break these
- NEVER use Streamlit вЂ” frontend is React + Tailwind, backend is FastAPI
- NEVER use cloud AI APIs (OpenAI, Gemini, Anthropic API) вЂ” all AI runs locally via Ollama
- NEVER use Google Fit API вЂ” it is deprecated. Use Health Connect API only
- NEVER store health data on any external server вЂ” everything stays local
- NEVER put all logic in one file вЂ” always use the service module pattern
- NEVER use sync functions where async is needed вЂ” FastAPI is fully async
- ALWAYS use Python type hints
- ALWAYS handle errors with proper try/except and return typed responses
- ALWAYS write code that works offline вЂ” no feature should require internet except SMS alerts

## Tech stack (locked вЂ” do not suggest alternatives)
Backend:
  - FastAPI (Python 3.11+) with uvicorn
  - SQLite via SQLAlchemy (async) for user data, records, appointments
  - InfluxDB client for vitals time-series data
  - WebSockets via FastAPI for real-time vitals streaming
  - MQTT via paho-mqtt for IoT device communication
  - JWT authentication via python-jose + passlib[bcrypt]
  - faster-whisper for Speech-to-Text (CUDA on RTX 4060)
  - Coqui TTS for Text-to-Speech (offline, Hindi primary)
  - silero-vad for Voice Activity Detection
  - ollama Python client for LLM inference (BioMistral / Llama 3.2)
  - bleak for direct BLE wearable communication
  - paho-mqtt for MQTT IoT protocol
  - fast2sms HTTP API for SMS alerts (India)
  - fpdf2 for PDF generation
  - python-jose[cryptography] for JWT

Frontend:
  - React 18 + TypeScript
  - Tailwind CSS for styling
  - Recharts for real-time vitals charts
  - WebSocket native API for live data
  - Axios for REST API calls

